   =20
      Legal hacking
   =20
 =20
If you want to hack into the computers of Apple Inc. or Meta Platforms Inc.=
 to steal their data, it is probably hard, because those companies have lot=
s of data and guard it jealously and have tons of money to hire really good=
 computer engineers. On the other hand, if you want to hack into the comput=
ers of a mid-sized suburban police department, it is probably=C2=A0easier, =
because running information security at a mid-sized suburban police departm=
ent is not the most glamorous job in tech. And then once you control a poli=
ce department email address, you just email Apple or Meta saying =E2=80=9Ch=
ello, this is the police, please give us your data for police reasons,=E2=
=80=9D and maybe that works. Here=E2=80=99s  an amazing story from Bloomber=
g=E2=80=99s William Turton:Apple Inc. and Meta Platforms Inc., the parent c=
ompany of Facebook, provided customer data to hackers who masqueraded as la=
w enforcement officials, according to three people with knowledge of the ma=
tter.Apple and Meta provided basic subscriber details, such as a customer=
=E2=80=99s address, phone number and IP address, in mid-2021 in response to=
 the forged =E2=80=9Cemergency data requests.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6The fraudul=
ent legal requests are part of a months-long campaign that targeted many te=
chnology companies and began as early as January 2021, according to two of =
the people. The forged legal requests are believed to be sent via hacked em=
ail domains belonging to law enforcement agencies in multiple countries, ac=
cording to the three people and an additional person investigating the matt=
er.=C2=A0The forged requests were made to appear legitimate. In some instan=
ces, the documents included the forged signatures of real or fictional law =
enforcement officers, according to two of the people. By compromising law e=
nforcement email systems, the hackers may have found legitimate legal reque=
sts and used them as a template to create forgeries, according to one of th=
e people. =E2=80=A6On Tuesday, Krebs on Security reported that hackers had =
forged an emergency data request to obtain information from the social medi=
a platform Discord. In a statement to Bloomberg, Discord confirmed that it =
had also fulfilled a forged legal request.=C2=A0=E2=80=9CWe verify these re=
quests by checking that they come from a genuine source, and did so in this=
 instance,=E2=80=9D Discord said in a statement. =E2=80=9CWhile our verific=
ation process confirmed that the law enforcement account itself was legitim=
ate, we later learned that it had been compromised by a malicious actor. We=
 have since conducted an investigation into this illegal activity and notif=
ied law enforcement about the compromised email account.=E2=80=9DRoughly sp=
eaking, the way to hack into a system is=C2=A0to find the part of the syste=
m that (1) has low levels of security but (2) has high levels of access. Th=
at might be the police.
